More Focus on the Union's Economy!
Printing New Notes Made Possible!
Tariffs on Imports to Increase?
Economy Preparing for War!
517
Union Government Funding Improved.
\tThe Federal Government has agreed to, and introduced, a number of new laws. These allow increased funding by the Government to cover the costs of the national crisis. The steps taken will allow the economic foundation stronger.\n\tThe new laws give the Government the authority to further improve funding, with new bills being drafted to allow the printing of new bank notes and to increase the tariffs imposed on foreign imports.\n\tMore controversially, the new laws are preparing the Union economy for war. Among the hot debates on the Senate floor, the status of southern property used to support the Union war effort has been discussed. This boils down to whether or not to respect the private property of the people who have openly rebelled against the United States. 
