The President Promoting the Commanding General.
\tTo increase the performance of Union armies, the U.S. Congress has passed an Act reviving the rank of Lieutenant General in the U.S. Army. Placing all armies effectively under a single command will allow better coordination within the theaters.\n\tThe previous general to hold this rank in the United States Army was none other than George Washington himself, while the hero of the Mexican War, Winfield Scott, held the rank of brevet Lieutenant General.\n\tSuch a drastic change in leadership will make the promoted general known throughout the nation, all eyes will be fixed on his leadership and efforts to finally end the war. With this fame also comes responsibility, as any failure will be judged harshly.\n\tThe President has made it clear that he appoints a man that he trusts to the job and the Lieutenant General has his full support. There will be no more changes in this position, unless the general in question is killed in action.
