\tConfederate politicians have agreed to support the nation's agricultural efforts with further funding. Increased subsidies will make plantations across the Confederacy more profitable, increasing agricultural output, especially that of cotton.\n\tAt the same time a proposition to weaponize cotton has been made. If the cotton trade to Europe were to cease, maybe the Europeans would be forced to intervene in the American Civil War on behalf of the Confederacy. The textile mills of the old continent require a constant flow of cotton any disruption would harm the profits of European industries.\n\tOne way to create an international cotton shortage would be to simply hold cotton at Confederate ports, in effect to hold King Cotton hostage in negotiations with the Europeans. If these measures are not sufficient, the last resort could be to burn the cotton stores this would surely make the threat of a cotton shortage a reality!
