The Confederacy Invests in Diplomacy!
\tThe Confederate States government is taking steps to improve their relations with European nations. More diplomats are sent across the Atlantic, with more access to resources, the aim is to increase trade and to encourage the European nations to recognize the Confederacy as an independent and sovereign nation among nations. Ultimately they want the Europeans to join them in their fight against their global opponent, the United States.\n\tWith a steady flow of government funds, in the form of subsidies, diplomats will keep improving relations and secure support for the South.\n\tAnother benefit will be the possibility of importing European weapons. The C.S. Army was created from scratch with few resources and available weaponry. The mass production of weapons in the Confederacy could be more expensive and time consuming than buying them directly from Europe. With the militias and the army growing, the importation of weapons will equip the mass of volunteers.
