The Confederacy Passes Tariff Act!
Tariff Rates Rising!
European Traders Shocked!


506
The Confederacy Passes Tariff Act!
\tThe Confederate government has passed an Act allowing large increases in the rates of tariffs imposed on foreign imports to the Confederacy. This Act will increase the funds collected from the mainly European trading partners bringing their products to Southern markets.\n\tWhile Government funding is improved, at least in the short term, the European nations have been left stupefied by the attack on their trade, and reports indicate that sympathy for the Confederate cause is decreasing in Europe.\n\tConfederate businesses, on the other hand, have welcomed the tariffs with open arms, as it helps domestic products to compete with foreign goods. The plantation owners are in a state of shock as low tariffs were previously used to keep the demand for Southern cotton in Europe high.
